## Domain -> Audit trail (unified review comments + build runs)

**Context**: Status-change comments lived only inside the per-version Validation timeline and the
build-run history lived in its own Runs page. Users wanted a single domain-wide activity feed that
interleaves both: every status switch (with its comment) and every build run + result.

**Changes**:
1. `src/back/objects/domain/Domain.py` — added `audit_trail_result(svc, *, limit)`: merges the
   review/validation event log (`list_review_events`, all versions) with the build-run history
   (`load_build_runs`) for the loaded domain and returns both streams raw (UI interleaves/sorts).
2. `src/api/routers/internal/domain.py` — new `GET /domain/audit-trail` endpoint (limit-capped)
   delegating to `Domain.audit_trail_result`.
3. `src/front/config/menu_config.json` — new "Audit trail" item (`id: audit`, `bi-journal-text`)
   under Domain -> Management, after Runs.
4. `src/front/templates/partials/domain/_domain_audit.html` (new) — header, All / Status & comments
   / Builds filter pills, and a timeline container.
5. `src/front/static/domain/js/domain-audit.js` (new) — fetches `/domain/audit-trail`, builds one
   newest-first timeline of review events (action, `from -> to` chip, comment, actor) and build runs
   (status, version, triples/duration/engine, message/error), with client-side filtering. Build
   entries reuse the run-details popup via `window.showRunDetailsObj`.
6. `src/front/static/domain/css/domain-audit.css` (new) — timeline marker/line/card styling.
7. `src/front/static/domain/js/domain-runs.js` — refactored `showRunDetails(idx)` into a reusable
   `showRunDetailsObj(run)` (exposed on `window`) so the audit timeline opens the same modal.
8. `src/front/templates/domain.html` — new `#audit-section` div, plus the audit CSS/JS includes.
9. `src/front/static/domain/js/domain.js` — load the audit trail when its section is activated.
10. `tests/units/domain/test_domain_service.py` — `TestAuditTrail` (merge shape, folder/limit
    forwarding, configured-registry and saved-domain guards).
11. `tests/units/api/test_ui_rendering.py` — `runs-section` / `audit-section` div checks and
    `test_audit_section_link_and_script` (sidebar link + `domain-audit.js` load).

**Modified files**:
- `src/back/objects/domain/Domain.py`
- `src/api/routers/internal/domain.py`
- `src/front/config/menu_config.json`
- `src/front/templates/partials/domain/_domain_audit.html` (new)
- `src/front/static/domain/js/domain-audit.js` (new)
- `src/front/static/domain/css/domain-audit.css` (new)
- `src/front/static/domain/js/domain-runs.js`
- `src/front/templates/domain.html`
- `src/front/static/domain/js/domain.js`
- `tests/units/domain/test_domain_service.py`
- `tests/units/api/test_ui_rendering.py`

**Test result**: `pytest tests/units --ignore=tests/property` -> 2282 passed, 11 skipped
(7 new tests). `node --check` clean on all touched JS files.

**Fix (same day)**: opening a build's details from the Audit trail froze the screen (dark backdrop,
no dialog). The run-details modal lived inside `#runs-section`, which is `display:none` whenever
another section is active, so Bootstrap showed the backdrop but the dialog stayed invisible. Moved
`#runDetailsModal` out of `partials/domain/_domain_runs.html` to page level in `domain.html` (outside
any `.sidebar-section`) so it opens correctly from both Runs and Audit trail.
- `src/front/templates/domain.html`
- `src/front/templates/partials/domain/_domain_runs.html`

**Deploy migration (same day)**: the `domain_review_events` table only existed in `schema.sql` and the
app's runtime self-heal. Added it to the idempotent owner-run migration block in
`scripts/bootstrap-lakebase-perms.sh` (Step 2b), which `scripts/deploy.sh` runs on every Lakebase
deploy — so redeploys provision the table reliably as the schema owner rather than relying on the
app SP's runtime CREATE. Verified via `make deploy`: both apps RUNNING and the migration logged
"schema migrations applied (domain_versions.status, build_runs, domain_review_events)" with
`domain_review_events` created fresh.
- `scripts/bootstrap-lakebase-perms.sh`

