## Audit trail & Runs — version dropdown filter

**Context**: Both the Audit trail and Runs sections showed every version at once. Users wanted to
filter by version, defaulting to the current version.

**Changes**:
1. `src/back/objects/domain/Domain.py` — `audit_trail_result` and `list_build_runs_result` now also
   return `versions` (`list_versions_sorted`) and `current_version` so the UI can build a dropdown.
2. `src/front/templates/partials/domain/_domain_audit.html` and `_domain_runs.html` — added a
   `<select>` version filter (defaults to "All versions", JS pre-selects the current version).
3. `src/front/static/domain/js/domain-audit.js` — fetches all versions once and filters the merged
   timeline (events + runs) client-side by the selected version; dropdown defaults to current.
4. `src/front/static/domain/js/domain-runs.js` — extracted `_renderRunsTable()` + `_populateRunsVersions()`;
   the table filters the cached runs client-side by the selected version (default current).
5. `tests/units/domain/test_domain_service.py` — `test_returns_versions_for_dropdown`.

**Modified files**:
- `src/back/objects/domain/Domain.py`
- `src/front/templates/partials/domain/_domain_audit.html`
- `src/front/templates/partials/domain/_domain_runs.html`
- `src/front/static/domain/js/domain-audit.js`
- `src/front/static/domain/js/domain-runs.js`
- `tests/units/domain/test_domain_service.py`

**Test result**: `pytest tests/units --ignore=tests/property` -> 2283 passed, 11 skipped.
`node --check` clean on both JS files.
